  "title": "La Rochefoucauld §laroch_076: There is real love just as there are real ghosts; every person speaks of it, ...",
  "body": "There is real love just as there are real ghosts; every person speaks of it, few persons have seen it. [\"Oh Love! no habitant of earth thou art-- An unseen seraph, we believe in thee-- A faith whose martyrs are the broken heart,-- But never yet hath seen, nor e'er shall see The naked eye, thy form as it should be.\" {--Lord Byron, }Childe Harold, {Canto} iv., stanza 121.]",
